transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I'm calling because I got an e-mail notification twice from my account with your services.

Speaker 2: And the heading says your order has a delivery exception.

Speaker 1: And then as you scroll down, it says there's a track order status, carrier message, facility, tracking number,

Speaker 2: carrier UPS, contact us number.

Speaker 1: So I'm calling to find out what this is about.

Speaker 2: It's almost certainly because of the snowstorm that's hitting most of the country.

Speaker 1: The mail has just been slowed down because the postal service is having issues.

Speaker 2: But what's your name and ZIP Code?

Speaker 1: I can take a look.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: ZIP Code 33755.

Speaker 2: Name is Joseph Guevara.

Speaker 1: I'll spell the last name.

Speaker 2: It's sort of G-U-E-V-A-R-A.

Speaker 1: G-U-E-V-A-R-A.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Can you spell it for me one more time?

Speaker 2: First or last name?

Speaker 1: The last name.

Speaker 2: G-U-E-V-A-R-A.

Speaker 1: Oh, that's why.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Belcher Road.

Speaker 2: Is that what it shows, Belcher Road?

Speaker 1: Oh, that's actually the PO box.

Speaker 2: The ZIP Code there is 33758.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I found you.

Speaker 2: The billing is the nursery road, right?

Speaker 1: Yes, that's the credit card that's paying for it.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so this is exactly what I thought, sir.

Speaker 2: So your package was most recently in North Carolina.

Speaker 1: With the snow that's going on, it's probably just stuck for a day or two.

Speaker 2: It is still on its way to you.

Speaker 1: That's all that's trying to say is that it's still going to be delivered.

Speaker 2: It's just stuck with the snowstorm right now.

Speaker 1: Okay, then can you tell me when it was shipped approximately?

Speaker 2: It was shipped on the 19th.

Speaker 1: So it was ordered on the 18th.

Speaker 2: It shipped on the 19th.

Speaker 1: Ordered on the 18th of January.

Speaker 2: Interesting, because I didn't place a – I didn't reorder.

Speaker 1: So how did that happen?

Speaker 2: You've been getting refills since you started, sir.

Speaker 1: So that was just your refill date.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I did not reorder.

Speaker 1: I wanted to stop it, and I was unable to when I went online.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you have to call us to do that.

Speaker 1: So if you want to close out the account permanently, I can do that for you.

Speaker 2: But it would close it out for good.

Speaker 1: Okay, good.

Speaker 2: Please do.

Speaker 1: Okay, then that's it.

Speaker 2: So this will be your last order that's shipped out.

Speaker 1: Okay, can you send me a confirmation of some kind about closing the account?

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: Will you send an email?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I got your email.

Speaker 1: I'll take care of that.

Speaker 2: Who am I speaking to?

Speaker 1: My name is John.

Speaker 2: John, okay.

Speaker 1: I should see the email in a few moments or tomorrow?

Speaker 2: Yeah, within a few moments.

Speaker 1: I just got to draft it and put it together, but it will take just a moment.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yep.

Speaker 2: Do you have a confirmation number?

Speaker 1: We don't have confirmation numbers on cancel, sir.

Speaker 2: Your account is closed, and I just sent the email.

Speaker 1: So if you have any other questions, I'm happy to help you,

Speaker 2: but I do have other calls that are waiting,

Speaker 1: so I can't just wait for the email to come through.

Speaker 2: When I want to reinstate an order, I just call you back and start it up again?

Speaker 1: No, there is no doing that.

Speaker 2: That's what I was saying.

Speaker 1: Well, I travel overseas, which is why I'm stopping it,

Speaker 2: because I'm not even going to be here.

Speaker 1: I understand that, sir.

Speaker 2: I understand.

Speaker 1: So I've stopped it, though, for you, and the email will confirm that as well.

Speaker 2: It should be to you by now.

Speaker 1: I hit send a moment ago.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: So if I want to restart it, how would I do that?

Speaker 2: Call us and see if we can do it for you.

Speaker 1: That's your best option.

Speaker 2: I can't promise we'll be able to do it.

Speaker 1: All righty.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: But give us a call.

Speaker 2: Have a good one.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Bye.
